problems.instructions:
CUDA API functions return cudaError_t.

Example:
cudaError_t err = cudaMalloc(...);
if (err != cudaSuccess) {
    printf("Error: %s\n", cudaGetErrorString(err));
}

In this problem:
1. Attempt to allocate device memory
2. Check the return value
3. If successful, print:
   Allocation successful
4. Free memory

This introduces basic runtime error handling.

